Lloyd Baker, Injury Attorney Phoenix, Scottsdale, Tempe


Practices : Business Laws, Personal Injury Matters  602-265-5555






Lloyd W. Baker’s philosophy is that, “We treat our clients as our friends.” This ideal ensures that the Las Vegas, personal injury attorneys at Lloyd Baker will always do what is best for our clients, and that they will be satisfied with our results. In return, we always have plenty of clients and friends who refer us business, trusting us with their own friends and family.
Lloyd graduated with honors from California State University-Northridge with a Bachelor of Science degree in Business Administration and Finance. He received his Juris Doctorate from the Brigham Young University Law School, which is consistently ranked among the top 25 law schools in the nation.
After law school, Lloyd worked for one of Nevada’s largest insurance defense law firms, practicing in the areas of medical malpractice and insurance defense for large corporate insurance companies. After his two-year association with this firm, Lloyd established his own law office and for more than a decade has been aggressively representing accident victims against those insurance corporations who take advantage of innocent injured victims.
Lloyd feels an enormous sense of satisfaction in righting a wrong and helping innocent people get back on their feet. He has represented victims of motorcycle and car accidents, dog bites and animal attacks, wrongful death, severe injuries and insurance bad faith.
As a skilled negotiator and litigator, Lloyd is committed to his clients whether the case is large or small, or is settled or pursued in court. Each year, he recovers tens of millions of dollars for his clients. Lloyd believes that each client should receive the most fair and generous compensation in the most timely manner to allow victims, their families and their loved ones to move on with their lives after a tragedy.
Along with his work as an attorney, Lloyd enjoys weight training, running and the martial arts. He loves spending time with his three beautiful daughters, whether it’s wakeboarding in the summer or riding dirt bikes and four-wheelers in the cooler months. He always finds time for his family and friends, as relationships are extremely important to him in both his personal life and his professional life.
If you were injured or a family member was killed in an accident that you believe was caused by the carelessness of another, please contact Lloyd Baker Injury Attorneys for your free, no-obligation consultation. Our Las Vegas, personal injury attorneys are ready to listen to your story and help you through this challenging time. We value lifelong clients, and if you have been injured in an accident we want to be the one firm you call.


 
