Product Liability Attorney Las Vegas NV
Home Product Liability Attorney Las Vegas NV 

 







Consumers should be able to expect that the products they purchase are safe when used as intended and according to directions.
The reality, however, is that thousands of people each year suffer injuries or wrongful death as a result of defective products. If you are injured by a defective product, the Las Vegas product liability lawyers at Lloyd Baker Attorneys may be able to help you pursue financial compensation or refer you to a qualified consumer class action attorney depending on the circumstances of your case.
Product designers, manufacturers, distributors and retailers have a responsibility to provide consumers with products that are free of potentially dangerous defects and contain appropriate instructions and warnings. Yet a simple act of carelessness at any point between a product’s design and sale can put consumers at risk for injury.
In product liability cases, negligence often relates to:

Defects in the design or engineering of a product prior to production
Faulty manufacturing or product assembly
Product tampering or unintentional contamination that results in a risk to consumers
Marketing flaws such as inadequate safety warnings or incomplete instructions

Examples of defective products that are commonly the focus of product liability lawsuits include:

Motor vehicles including cars, trucks, motorcycles and all-terrain vehicles
Motor vehicle parts
Medical devices
Prescription drugs
Household appliances
Toys and recreational gear

To learn more, please see Questions about Product Liability and Defective Products.
If you were hurt or a family member suffered wrongful death as a result of a defective product, please contact Lloyd Baker Attorneys for your free case consultation. Our Las Vegas product liability attorneys are ready to listen to your story and offer you the legal support you need. We value lifelong clients, if you have been injured in an accident we want to be the one firm you call.





 
